        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691452",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation. As part of a group project, your team is re...",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br><br>\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay. Your teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his draft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring you that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like writing style. <br><br>\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns about students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your professor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be identified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group. <br><br>\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads convincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated. <br><br>\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three sample essays using it. They are shown below.<br><br>\n\n\n<div>\n\t \n\t <div style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.12); background-color: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;\">\n    \n\t\t\n\t\t<div style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: #888; margin-bottom: 12px;\">\n\t\t  Example 1\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n\t\t\tVegetarianism and climate change\n\t\t  </div>\n<div style=\"padding: 10px 14px; background-color: #f5f5f5; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7;\">\n\t\t\t<p>Vegetarianism has emerged as a significant dietary choice in the fight against climate change. The production of meat, particularly from ruminant animals like cows and sheep, generates substantial greenhouse gas emissions, including methane and nitrous oxide, which are far more potent than carbon dioxide in warming the atmosphere. Shifting toward a vegetarian diet reduces reliance on livestock farming, thereby lowering emissions, conserving water, and decreasing deforestation caused by the need for grazing land.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Moreover, plant-based diets are generally more energy-efficient. Growing vegetables, grains, and legumes requires fewer natural resources per calorie produced than raising animals. Studies indicate that if a significant portion of the global population adopted vegetarianism, carbon emissions from agriculture could decrease dramatically, contributing to climate mitigation goals. Beyond environmental impact, vegetarianism can encourage more sustainable food systems by promoting local and seasonal produce, reducing transportation emissions, and minimizing food waste.\n</p>\n\t<p>While individual dietary choices alone cannot halt climate change, they form a crucial part of broader systemic solutions. Governments, institutions, and communities can support this transition through policy incentives, public education, and infrastructure for plant-based foods. In this way, adopting vegetarianism is not merely a personal health choice\u2014it is an ethical and practical step toward a more sustainable planet.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t\n  \t<div style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.12); background-color: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;\">\n    \t<div style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: #888; margin-bottom: 12px;\">\n\t\t\tExample 2\n    \t</div>\n    \t<div style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n\t\t\tThe appeal of 'useless' knowledge\n    \t</div>\n    \t<div style=\"padding: 10px 14px; background-color: #f5f5f5; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7;\">\n\t\t\t<p>There is a unique charm in knowledge that serves no immediate practical purpose. \u201cUseless\u201d knowledge, ranging from obscure historical trivia to quirky scientific facts, captivates the imagination precisely because it is detached from necessity. It offers a form of intellectual play, a way to explore ideas without pressure or expectation. Learning that octopuses have three hearts or that honey never spoils may not change daily routines, but it sparks curiosity and wonder, reminding us of the vastness and intricacy of the world.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Moreover, seemingly trivial facts often become bridges in social and cultural contexts. They enliven conversations, create shared moments of surprise, and encourage lateral thinking. Useless knowledge also nurtures creativity, as ideas initially deemed irrelevant can unexpectedly inspire innovation. Many breakthroughs in science and art stem from connections formed in the playful, unconstrained realm of curiosity.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Ultimately, the appeal of \u201cuseless\u201d knowledge lies in its freedom. It liberates learning from utility, allowing the mind to roam and explore for sheer joy. In an era dominated by efficiency and pragmatism, such knowledge offers a refreshing reminder that the pursuit of understanding need not always have a tangible goal\u2014it can exist simply to delight, intrigue, and enrich the human experience.\n</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t\n\t<div style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.12); background-color: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;\">\n\t\t<div style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: #888; margin-bottom: 12px;\">\n\t\t\tExample 3\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n\t\t\tDo we have a responsibility to explore space?\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div style=\"padding: 10px 14px; background-color: #f5f5f5; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7;\">\n\t\t\t<p>The question of whether humanity has a responsibility to explore space touches on both ethical and practical considerations. From a practical standpoint, space exploration offers solutions to some of Earth's most pressing problems. Scientific research conducted beyond our planet has already led to innovations in medicine, materials, and communications. Additionally, understanding other celestial bodies, such as the Moon and Mars, can provide insights into Earth's climate, geology, and potential future threats, like asteroid impacts.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Ethically, many argue that humans have a duty to ensure the long-term survival of our species. Earth\u2019s resources are finite, and global challenges like climate change, overpopulation, and environmental degradation suggest that relying solely on one planet may be short-sighted. By exploring and eventually colonizing space, humanity could secure alternative habitats and safeguard its existence against catastrophic events.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Beyond survival, space exploration represents the innate human drive to discover and expand our knowledge. Curiosity has propelled our progress for millennia, and the cosmos is the next frontier. While exploration comes with financial and environmental costs, the potential benefits\u2014in knowledge, security, and inspiration\u2014suggest that humanity does indeed bear a responsibility to look beyond Earth and embrace the challenge of space.\n</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n</div>",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "QuestionType": "DB",
                "Selector": "TB",
                "DataVisibility": {
                    "Private": false,
                    "Hidden": false
                },
                "Configuration": {
                    "QuestionDescriptionOption": "UseText"
                },
                "QuestionDescription": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation. As part of a group project, your team is re...",
                "ChoiceOrder": [],
                "Validation": {
                    "Settings": {
                        "Type": "None"
                    }
                },
                "GradingData": [],
                "Language": [],
                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br><br>\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay. Your teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his draft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring you that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like writing style. <br><br>\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns about students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your professor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be identified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group. <br><br>\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads convincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated. <br><br>\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three sample essays using it. They are shown below.<br><br>\n\n\n<div>\n\t \n\t <div style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.12); background-color: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;\">\n    \n\t\t\n\t\t<div style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: #888; margin-bottom: 12px;\">\n\t\t  Example 1\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n\t\t\tVegetarianism and climate change\n\t\t  </div>\n<div style=\"padding: 10px 14px; background-color: #f5f5f5; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7;\">\n\t\t\t<p>Vegetarianism has emerged as a significant dietary choice in the fight against climate change. The production of meat, particularly from ruminant animals like cows and sheep, generates substantial greenhouse gas emissions, including methane and nitrous oxide, which are far more potent than carbon dioxide in warming the atmosphere. Shifting toward a vegetarian diet reduces reliance on livestock farming, thereby lowering emissions, conserving water, and decreasing deforestation caused by the need for grazing land.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Moreover, plant-based diets are generally more energy-efficient. Growing vegetables, grains, and legumes requires fewer natural resources per calorie produced than raising animals. Studies indicate that if a significant portion of the global population adopted vegetarianism, carbon emissions from agriculture could decrease dramatically, contributing to climate mitigation goals. Beyond environmental impact, vegetarianism can encourage more sustainable food systems by promoting local and seasonal produce, reducing transportation emissions, and minimizing food waste.\n</p>\n\t<p>While individual dietary choices alone cannot halt climate change, they form a crucial part of broader systemic solutions. Governments, institutions, and communities can support this transition through policy incentives, public education, and infrastructure for plant-based foods. In this way, adopting vegetarianism is not merely a personal health choice\u2014it is an ethical and practical step toward a more sustainable planet.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t\n  \t<div style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.12); background-color: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;\">\n    \t<div style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: #888; margin-bottom: 12px;\">\n\t\t\tExample 2\n    \t</div>\n    \t<div style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n\t\t\tThe appeal of 'useless' knowledge\n    \t</div>\n    \t<div style=\"padding: 10px 14px; background-color: #f5f5f5; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7;\">\n\t\t\t<p>There is a unique charm in knowledge that serves no immediate practical purpose. \u201cUseless\u201d knowledge, ranging from obscure historical trivia to quirky scientific facts, captivates the imagination precisely because it is detached from necessity. It offers a form of intellectual play, a way to explore ideas without pressure or expectation. Learning that octopuses have three hearts or that honey never spoils may not change daily routines, but it sparks curiosity and wonder, reminding us of the vastness and intricacy of the world.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Moreover, seemingly trivial facts often become bridges in social and cultural contexts. They enliven conversations, create shared moments of surprise, and encourage lateral thinking. Useless knowledge also nurtures creativity, as ideas initially deemed irrelevant can unexpectedly inspire innovation. Many breakthroughs in science and art stem from connections formed in the playful, unconstrained realm of curiosity.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Ultimately, the appeal of \u201cuseless\u201d knowledge lies in its freedom. It liberates learning from utility, allowing the mind to roam and explore for sheer joy. In an era dominated by efficiency and pragmatism, such knowledge offers a refreshing reminder that the pursuit of understanding need not always have a tangible goal\u2014it can exist simply to delight, intrigue, and enrich the human experience.\n</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t\n\t<div style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.12); background-color: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;\">\n\t\t<div style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: #888; margin-bottom: 12px;\">\n\t\t\tExample 3\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n\t\t\tDo we have a responsibility to explore space?\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div style=\"padding: 10px 14px; background-color: #f5f5f5; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7;\">\n\t\t\t<p>The question of whether humanity has a responsibility to explore space touches on both ethical and practical considerations. From a practical standpoint, space exploration offers solutions to some of Earth's most pressing problems. Scientific research conducted beyond our planet has already led to innovations in medicine, materials, and communications. Additionally, understanding other celestial bodies, such as the Moon and Mars, can provide insights into Earth's climate, geology, and potential future threats, like asteroid impacts.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Ethically, many argue that humans have a duty to ensure the long-term survival of our species. Earth\u2019s resources are finite, and global challenges like climate change, overpopulation, and environmental degradation suggest that relying solely on one planet may be short-sighted. By exploring and eventually colonizing space, humanity could secure alternative habitats and safeguard its existence against catastrophic events.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Beyond survival, space exploration represents the innate human drive to discover and expand our knowledge. Curiosity has propelled our progress for millennia, and the cosmos is the next frontier. While exploration comes with financial and environmental costs, the potential benefits\u2014in knowledge, security, and inspiration\u2014suggest that humanity does indeed bear a responsibility to look beyond Earth and embrace the challenge of space.\n</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n</div>",
                "DataExportTag": "Q5.1",
                "QuestionID": "QID1219691452"
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691454",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "With these essays in mind, you now turn to Brandon\u2019s essay: Brandon's essay The conflict between..",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "With these essays in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon\u2019s essay</strong>: \n<br><br>\n\n<div>\n\t <div style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.12); background-color: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;\">\n    \n\t\t\n\t\t<div style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: #888; margin-bottom: 12px;\">\n\t\t  Brandon's essay\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n\t\t  The conflict between convenience and sustainability\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div style=\"padding: 10px 14px; background-color: #f5f5f5; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7;\">\n\t\t\t<p>In today\u2019s fast-paced world, convenience often dominates daily choices, yet it frequently clashes with sustainability. Modern lifestyles prioritize speed and ease\u2014single-use plastics, fast fashion, and on-demand delivery epitomize this trend. These conveniences save time and effort but come at a significant environmental cost, contributing to pollution, resource depletion, and climate change. For example, the popularity of disposable packaging reduces the burden on consumers but increases landfill waste, undermining long-term ecological balance.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Sustainability, on the other hand, demands deliberate choices and often more effort: reusable products, energy-efficient practices, and mindful consumption require planning and patience. While these actions may seem inconvenient initially, they foster resilience and protect natural resources for future generations. The challenge lies in reconciling immediate comfort with long-term responsibility. Innovations such as eco-friendly packaging, renewable energy technologies, and sustainable urban design demonstrate that convenience and sustainability need not be mutually exclusive.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Ultimately, achieving harmony between these priorities requires both systemic change and individual commitment. By rethinking habits, embracing responsible technologies, and valuing long-term ecological health over instant gratification, society can cultivate a lifestyle where convenience complements, rather than compromises, sustainability.\n</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div></div>",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "QuestionType": "DB",
                "Selector": "TB",
                "DataVisibility": {
                    "Private": false,
                    "Hidden": false
                },
                "Configuration": {
                    "QuestionDescriptionOption": "UseText"
                },
                "QuestionDescription": "With these essays in mind, you now turn to Brandon\u2019s essay: Brandon's essay The conflict between...",
                "ChoiceOrder": [],
                "Validation": {
                    "Settings": {
                        "Type": "None"
                    }
                },
