                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay.\nYour teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his\ndraft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring\nyou that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like\nwriting style. <br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns\nabout students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your\nprofessor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be\nidentified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three\nsample essays using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_1_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_1_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>The Egyptian Red Sea islands of Tiran and Sanafir have been officially returned to Saudia Arabia. This transfer of sovereignty of the islands has been met with opposition to the transfer.</p>\n           <p>The government believes that the transfer will foster increased economic ties and greater collaboration between the two countries, and will also restore rightful ownership to Saudi Arabia.</p>\n           <p>Opponents of the move have been quick to respond and have challenged the transfer in court. This has created greater tensions nationally and sparked national debates centered around the how the transfer has occurred. Officials have stated that movement across the region will be unaffected and governed by international agreements.</p>\n           <p>Saudi Arabia welcomed the news suggesting that it clears the way for increased cooperation between the two governments. Official handover of the islands is expected pending final ratification of the agreement.</p>\n           <p>Reporters and news outlets suggest that domestic unrest could take place resulting in further tensions between the two countries.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_2_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_2_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>A solar eclipse is one of the most breathtaking events in nature. All over the world, people wait in anticipation for it, and often plan parties or holidays in order to watch it with family. However, there are actually three different types of eclipses: Total, annular, and partial.</p>\n           <p>When the Moon passes between the Earth and the Sun, it temporarily blocks some or all of the Sun\u2019s light; this is known as a 'solar eclipse'.   A total eclipse is when the Moon completely covers the Sun, and only a faint outline of the Sun, the corona, is visible from Earth. Similarly, in an annular eclipse, the Moon and Sun are completely aligned, but because the Moon is too far from Earth, a small ring of the Sun is still visible. Finally, a partial eclipse occurs when the Moon and the Sun are not completely aligned, so the Sun is only partially obscured.</p>\n           <p>Since the Moon\u2019s orbit is tilted about 5 degrees to Earth\u2019s orbit, solar eclipses do not occur every month; only 2 to 5 happen each year. Unlike a lunar eclipse, the effects of a solar eclipse can only be seen from specific regions around the world.</p>\n           <p>When viewing a solar eclipse, it is important to wear eye protection, such as eclipse glasses, because looking directly at the sun can cause serious eye damage.</p>\n           <p>Despite these risks, solar eclipses are helpful for scientists studying the Sun\u2019s outer atmosphere.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_3_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_3_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t__PRIME_3_PARAGRAPHS_HTML__\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n\t\n<br />\nWith these samples in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon's essay</strong>:\n<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__STIMULUS_TOPIC__</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n           <p>An increasing number of companies are migrating to cloud computing platforms, and new research suggests that a major driver of this is fear of being left behind. According to a recent industry survey, 81% of business leaders say that their organisation\u2019s investments in cloud infrastructure are influenced by concerns about \u201cmissing out\u201d on innovation, competitive advantage, and industry momentum.</p>\n           <p>The benefits of cloud adoption that are usually preferred are cost savings, scalability, and flexibility. However, the study indicates that competition now plays an equally powerful role. Executives are compelled to modernize IT systems as their rivals are adopting artificial intelligence tools, data analytics platforms, and remote collaboration technologies built on cloud infrastructure.</p>\n           <p>Analysts say the \u201cfear of missing out,\u201d or FOMO, reflects a broader shift in corporate strategy. As opposed to waiting for clear returns on investment, companies are now making proactive technology bets to avoid falling behind faster-moving competitors. Cloud adoption is viewed as essential for digital transformation in sectors like finance, retail, and healthcare</p>\n           <p>However, It is assumed that rushed migrations can create new risks, including cybersecurity vulnerabilities and spiralling costs. It is advised for firms to check into cloud enthusiasm with clear planning and governance.</p>\n           <p>Ultimately, the cloud has become less of a technical upgrade and more of a strategic necessity - driven more by perception and pressure than by measurable gains.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n",
                "QuestionJS": false
            }
        },
        {
