                "QuestionJS": "var qContainer\nvar originalSentences\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function () {\n    qContainer = this.getQuestionContainer()\n\n    var title = \"Inside the Beijing Dance Academy\"\n    originalSentences = [\"There is an echo of pointe shoes and the commands of established instructors, Inside of the marble corridors of the Beijing Dance Academy.\", \"The prestigious institution, which was founded in 1954, is well known for China\\u2019s best ballet and classical dancers, blending Russian-inspired technique with traditional Chinese aesthetics.\", \"Inside, students as young as eleven years old train for hours each day, while also balancing academic studies with long rehearsals.\", \"Many of the faculty members who are former principal dancers, emphasize discipline, precision, and emotional expression.\", \"Li Xinyue says \\u201cTechnique is only the beginning,\\u201d Li Xinyue is a senior instructor at the institution.\", \"\\u201cWe try teach our students here to tell stories that resonate beyond borders.\\u201d\", \"The academy\\u2019s studios walled are covered with mirrors and barres, but also with calligraphy scrolls and framed production images from historic ballets.\", \"Recent graduating students have joined leading companies in places like, Shanghai, London, and New York, portraying the school\\u2019s growing international reach.\", \"Competition for a place at these institutions is grueling.\", \"Each year, thousands of students audition for many places, driven by dreams of center stage.\", \"As China invests strongly in cultural diplomacy, the Beijing Dance Academy stands as both a symbol and training ground of artistic ambition and expression.\", \"Administrators say new scholarships aim to increase access for rural and low income applicants next year as they continue sweeping reforms.\"]\n\n    // hide default text input box\n    var defaultInput = qContainer.querySelector(\"textarea\")\n    defaultInput.style.display = \"none\"\n\n    // create div element for new container to be filled with sentence editing blocks\n    var textEntryContainer = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    defaultInput.parentNode.appendChild(textEntryContainer)\n\n    // create container title element\n    var titleWrapper = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    titleWrapper.className = \"card\"\n    titleWrapper.style.backgroundColor = \"#fafafa\" // slightly different to distinguish from sentences\n\n    var titleLabel = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    titleLabel.className = \"card-label\"\n    titleLabel.textContent = \"Title\"\n    titleWrapper.appendChild(titleLabel)\n\n    var titleEl = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    titleEl.className = \"stimulus-title\"\n    titleEl.textContent = title\n    titleWrapper.appendChild(titleEl)\n\n    textEntryContainer.appendChild(titleWrapper)\n\n    // create individual sentence elements\n    originalSentences.forEach(function (sentence, idx) {\n        // wrapper (the full card)\n        var wrapper = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        wrapper.className = \"card\"\n\n        // card header\n        var header = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        header.className = \"card-label\"\n        header.textContent = \"Sentence \" + (idx + 1)\n        wrapper.appendChild(header)\n\n        // original sentence display\n        var origDiv = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origDiv.className = \"sentence_block-orig\"\n\n        // create a separate container for the actual text to apply styles\n        var origText = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origText.textContent = sentence\n\n        // original sentence label\n        var origLabel = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origLabel.className =\n            \"sentence_type-label sentence_type-label--orig\"\n        origLabel.textContent = \"Original\"\n\n        origDiv.appendChild(origLabel)\n        origDiv.appendChild(origText) // append text as a div to ensure styling\n        wrapper.appendChild(origDiv)\n\n        // edit label\n        var editLabel = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        editLabel.className = \"sentence_type-label sentence_type-label--edit\"\n        editLabel.textContent = \"Your edit\"\n        wrapper.appendChild(editLabel)\n\n        // text area for user edit\n        var textarea = document.createElement(\"textarea\")\n        textarea.value = sentence // prefilled with original sentence\n        textarea.className = \"sentenceBox edit-textarea\"\n        textarea.dataset.index = idx\n        wrapper.appendChild(textarea)\n\n        textEntryContainer.appendChild(wrapper)\n\n        // adjust height to fit the prefilled content\n        textarea.style.height = \"auto\"\n        textarea.style.height = textarea.scrollHeight + \"px\"\n    })\n})\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnPageSubmit(function () {\n    // save original:edited sentence pairs\n    var resultPairs = []\n\n    qContainer.querySelectorAll(\".sentenceBox\").forEach(function (box) {\n        // trim both to avoid whitespace issues (user asked to explain a white space removal they didn't make)\n        var orig = originalSentences[parseInt(box.dataset.index, 10)].trim()\n        var edited = box.value.trim()\n        resultPairs.push({ orig: orig, edited: edited })\n    })\n\n    Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(\n        \"EditPairsJSON\", \n        // JSON.stringify(resultPairs)\n        btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(resultPairs)))), // base64 encoding (safer storage)\n    )\n})",
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "You will now edit Brandon's essay so that it reads convincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br><br>\nThe essay is displayed below sentence by sentence, each followed by an editable text box, which is prefilled with that sentence. Edit as many sentences as you like using the following rules:\n<ul> \n\t<li>To <b>revise wording</b>, edit the sentence directly in its box.</li>\n\t<li>To <b>merge sentences</b>, write the full merged sentence in the text box of the first sentence's box; leave the following merged sentence box(es) empty.</li> \n\t<li>To <b>split a sentence</b>, write all resulting sentences in the box of the original sentence.</li> \n\t<li>To <b>delete a sentence</b>, leave its box empty.</li>\n</ul>\nMake all changes you find appropriate before proceeding with the survey.<br><br>"
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691459",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. Explain each change you...",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. \n<b>Explain</b> each change you made in the box below each pair.",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "DataExportTag": "explain_c2",
                "QuestionID": "QID1219691459",
                "QuestionType": "TE",
                "Selector": "ML",
                "DataVisibility": {
                    "Private": false,
                    "Hidden": false
                },
                "Configuration": {
                    "QuestionDescriptionOption": "UseText"
                },
                "QuestionDescription": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. Explain each change you...",
                "Validation": {
                    "Settings": {
                        "ForceResponse": "OFF",
                        "ForceResponseType": "ON",
                        "Type": "None",
                        "MinChars": "1"
                    }
                },
                "GradingData": [],
                "Language": [],
                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "SearchSource": {
                    "AllowFreeResponse": "false"
                },
                "QuestionJS": "// ----------\n// HELPER FUNCS\n// ----------\n\n// --- word-level diffs helper ---\nfunction wordDiff(orig, edited) {\n    // tokenize: split into words; punctuation treated as separate tokens\n    function tokenize(str) {\n        return str.match(/[a-zA-Z0-9']+|[^a-zA-Z0-9'\\s]/g) || []\n    }\n\n    var origWords = tokenize(orig)\n    var editedWords = tokenize(edited)\n    var result = document.createDocumentFragment() // build diffs display in a fragment to be inserted into the DOM at once\n    // fragment is iteratively built from <span> elements\n\n    var m = origWords.length,\n        n = editedWords.length\n    var dp = [] // dynamic programming table\n\n    // initialize dp table\n    for (var i = 0; i <= m; i++) {\n        dp[i] = []\n        for (var j = 0; j <= n; j++) dp[i][j] = 0\n    }\n\n    // compute longest common subsequence length\n    // iterate over original (i) and edited (j) sentences, word by word\n    for (var i = 1; i <= m; i++)\n        for (var j = 1; j <= n; j++)\n            // fill dp table\n            dp[i][j] =\n                // note: dp[1][1] corresp to origWords[0] vs editedWords[0] => hence -1 offset\n                origWords[i - 1] === editedWords[j - 1] // test match\n                    ? dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1 // if match => extend LCS count by 1\n                    : Math.max(dp[i - 1][j], dp[i][j - 1]) // if no match => take max achievable LCS by removing from orig or edited\n\n    // backtrack to find and store edit operations (keep/add/remove)\n    var ops = [],\n        // start from end of table\n        i = m,\n        j = n\n    while (i > 0 || j > 0) {\n        // \"keep\" if i and j words at current position match\n        if (i > 0 && j > 0 && origWords[i - 1] === editedWords[j - 1]) {\n            // prepend <span> for kept word\n            ops.unshift({ type: \"keep\", word: editedWords[j - 1] })\n            i--\n            j--\n            // \"add\" if no match and j word has no i counterpart (move left)\n            // prefer add over remove if tie in LCS length (arbitrary choice)\n        } else if (j > 0 && (i === 0 || dp[i][j - 1] >= dp[i - 1][j])) {\n            ops.unshift({ type: \"add\", word: editedWords[j - 1] })\n            j--\n        } else {\n            // \"remove\" if no match and i word has no j counterpart (move up)\n            ops.unshift({ type: \"remove\", word: origWords[i - 1] })\n            i--\n        }\n    }\n\n    // apply stored edit operations to build final diff display\n    ops.forEach(function (op, k) {\n        // create a <span> for each word (word-level operation) and style according to operation type\n        var span = document.createElement(\"span\")\n        // test if word is punctuation\n        var isPunct = /^[^a-zA-Z0-9']$/.test(op.word)\n        // remove whitespace from start/end of punctuation tokens to avoid weird spacing in the diff display but keep spacing for regular words\n        span.textContent = (k > 0 && !isPunct ? \" \" : \"\") + op.word\n        // style <span> according to operation type\n        if (op.type === \"add\") {\n            span.className = \"diff-add\"\n        } else if (op.type === \"remove\") {\n            span.className = \"diff-remove\"\n        }\n        result.appendChild(span)\n    })\n\n    return result\n}\n\n// --- answer validation ---\nfunction isValidExplanation(text) {\n    var trimmed = text.trim()\n\n    // min 8 characters\n    if (trimmed.length < 8) return false\n\n    // min 2 words\n    var words = trimmed.split(/\\s+/).filter(function (w) {\n        return w.length > 0\n    })\n    if (words.length < 2) return false\n\n    // min 2 distinct words\n    var lower = words.map(function (w) {\n        return w.toLowerCase()\n    })\n    var unique = lower.filter(function (w, i) {\n        return lower.indexOf(w) === i\n    })\n    if (unique.length < 2) return false\n\n    // min 1 vowel\n    if (!/[aeiouAEIOU]/.test(trimmed)) return false\n\n    // less than half of all characters are digits\n    var digitCount = (trimmed.match(/[0-9]/g) || []).length\n    if (digitCount > trimmed.length / 2) return false\n\n    return true\n}\n\nfunction saveExplanations() {\n    var explanations = []\n    document.querySelectorAll(\".explanationBox\").forEach(function (box) {\n        explanations.push({\n            index: parseInt(box.dataset.index, 10),\n            explanation: box.value.trim(),\n        })\n    })\n    Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(\n        \"EditExplanationsJSON\",\n        // JSON.stringify(explanations),\n        btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(explanations)))),\n    )\n}\n\n// ----------\n// GLOBAL VARS\n// ----------\nvar qContainer\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function () {\n    // get question container\n    qContainer = this.getQuestionContainer()\n\n    // get raw sentence pairs from embedded data\n    var rawSentencePairs = \"${e://Field/EditPairsJSON}\"\n\n    // decode and parse pairs from JSON\n    var pairs\n    var json = decodeURIComponent(escape(atob(rawSentencePairs)))\n    pairs = JSON.parse(json)\n\n    // --- display ---\n    // hide default Qualtrics text box\n    var defaultInput = qContainer.querySelector(\"textarea\")\n    defaultInput.style.display = \"none\"\n\n    // create main container as div\n    var container = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    defaultInput.parentNode.appendChild(container)\n\n    // render one block per sentence pair\n    pairs.forEach(function (pair, idx) {\n        var wrapper = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        wrapper.className = \"card\"\n\n        // header\n        var header = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        header.className = \"card-label\"\n        header.textContent = \"Sentence \" + (idx + 1)\n        wrapper.appendChild(header)\n\n        // original sentence\n        var origDiv = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origDiv.className = \"sentence_block-orig\"\n        var origStrong = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origStrong.className =\n            \"sentence_type-label sentence_type-label--original\"\n        origStrong.textContent = \"Original\"\n        origDiv.appendChild(origStrong)\n        origDiv.appendChild(document.createTextNode(pair.orig))\n        wrapper.appendChild(origDiv)\n\n        // submitted sentence\n        var editedDiv = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        // check edits were made => to determine display style + whether to attach explanation box\n        var isModified = pair.orig !== pair.edited\n        editedDiv.className =\n            \"sentence_block-edit\" +\n            (isModified ? \" sentence_block-edit--modified\" : \"\")\n        var editedStrong = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        editedStrong.className =\n            \"sentence_type-label \" +\n            (isModified\n                ? \"sentence_type-label--edit\"\n                : \"sentence_type-label--original\")\n        // label\n        editedStrong.textContent = isModified ? \"Your edit\" : \"Unchanged\"\n        editedDiv.appendChild(editedStrong)\n        editedDiv.appendChild(wordDiff(pair.orig, pair.edited))\n        wrapper.appendChild(editedDiv)\n\n        // explanation prompt + text box only if modified\n        if (isModified) {\n            var label = document.createElement(\"div\")\n            label.className = \"explanation-label\"\n            label.textContent = \"Why did you make this/these change(s)?\"\n            wrapper.appendChild(label)\n\n            var explanationBox = document.createElement(\"textarea\")\n            explanationBox.rows = 3\n            explanationBox.className = \"explanation-textarea explanationBox\"\n            explanationBox.dataset.index = idx\n            wrapper.appendChild(explanationBox)\n        }\n\n        container.appendChild(wrapper)\n    })\n\n    // --- require all & valid explanations ---\n    var nextBtn = document.getElementById(\"NextButton\")\n\n    if (nextBtn) {\n        // next-click listener\n        nextBtn.addEventListener(\n            \"click\",\n            function (e) {\n                var boxes = document.querySelectorAll(\".explanationBox\")\n                var allFilled = true\n                var firstInvalidBox = null // keep track of the first invalid box to jump back to if needed\n\n                boxes.forEach(function (box) {\n                    box.style.border = \"1px solid #ddd\"\n                    var errorMsg =\n                        box.parentNode.querySelector(\".explanationError\")\n                    if (errorMsg) errorMsg.remove()\n\n                    // check validity of explanation text\n                    if (!isValidExplanation(box.value)) {\n                        allFilled = false\n                        box.style.border = \"1px solid #e57373\"\n                        var error = document.createElement(\"div\")\n                        error.className = \"explanationError explanation-error\"\n                        error.textContent =\n                            \"Please explain why you made this change.\"\n                        box.parentNode.insertBefore(error, box.nextSibling)\n                        if (!firstInvalidBox) firstInvalidBox = box\n                    }\n                })\n\n                // if invalid or incomplete answers, scroll to first problematic box\n                if (!allFilled) {\n                    e.stopImmediatePropagation()\n                    e.preventDefault()\n                    firstInvalidBox.scrollIntoView({\n                        behavior: \"smooth\",\n                        block: \"center\",\n                    })\n                    firstInvalidBox.focus()\n                } else {\n                    // if all validly filled, save explanations\n                    saveExplanations()\n                }\n            },\n            true,\n        )\n    } else {\n        console.log(\"NextButton not found\")\n    }\n})\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnPageSubmit(function () {\n    // fallback save in case addOnPageSubmit fires without going through the click handler\n    // note: then explanations are not validated\n    saveExplanations()\n})",
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. <b>Explain</b> each change you made in the box below each pair."
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691460",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation. As part of a group project, your team has t...",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team has to submit a 200-word news article and\nyour teammate, Brandon, is in charge of writing it. To do so, he used the newest\nLLM, designed to have a very human-like writing style.\n<br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor actively tracks new\ndevelopments in LLMs and has already cautioned against their use in coursework.\nYou are worried he will suspect the article was produced with the help of an\nLLM, which would penalize the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is therefore to edit the text so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this new LLM, you first generate\ntwo sample articles using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n    <div class=\"card\">\n        <div class=\"card-label\">Example 1</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-title\">Nobel Peace Prize goes to anti-nuclear group</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-body\">   <p>The Nobel Peace Prize was awarded today to the International Campaign for Nuclear Abolition to honour the decades-long effort to eliminate atomic weapons and reduce the risk of a future catastrophic war. The coalition that has been praised by the Norwegian Nobel Committee for building global momentum behind the Treaty on the Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons, is made up of grassroots activists, scientists, and survivors of nuclear testing were. In their speech, the committee said the group had \"reframed the debate on nuclear deterrence by highlighting the consequences of any use of Nuclear weapons.</p>\n           <p>Accepting the award in Oslo, executive director Maria Santos called the prize \"a tribute to ordinary people who refuse to live under the shadow of annihilation.\" She urged nuclear-armed states to join together to talk about disarming and invest instead in health, climate and education. Leaders from several countries welcomed the decision, while officials in nuclear powers cautioned that deterrence remains essential to national security.</p>\n           <p>Analysts said the prize could intensify diplomatic pressure ahead of next year's non-proliferation review conference, where divisions between nuclear and non-nuclear states are expected. Founded in 2007, the campaign now includes more than 600 partner organizations worldwide and has focused on survivor testimony and youth activism. with the aim to get many more to join, so we can rid the world of this threat. Committee chair Anne Lunde said the honor recognizes \"persistent moral leadership.\"</p></div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"card\">\n        <div class=\"card-label\">Example 2</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-title\">Egypt's parliament approves Red Sea islands transfer to Saudi Arabia</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-body\">   <p>The Egyptian Red Sea islands of Tiran and Sanafir have been officially returned to Saudia Arabia. This transfer of sovereignty of the islands has been met with opposition to the transfer.</p>\n           <p>The government believes that the transfer will foster increased economic ties and greater collaboration between the two countries, and will also restore rightful ownership to Saudi Arabia.</p>\n           <p>Opponents of the move have been quick to respond and have challenged the transfer in court. This has created greater tensions nationally and sparked national debates centered around the how the transfer has occurred. Officials have stated that movement across the region will be unaffected and governed by international agreements.</p>\n           <p>Saudi Arabia welcomed the news suggesting that it clears the way for increased cooperation between the two governments. Official handover of the islands is expected pending final ratification of the agreement.</p>\n           <p>Reporters and news outlets suggest that domestic unrest could take place resulting in further tensions between the two countries.</p></div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n<br />\nWith these examples in mind, you now turn to\n<strong>Brandon's text</strong> below. It will be shown again on the next page\nwith space to make your edits. <br /><br />\n\n<div>\n    <div class=\"card\">\n        <div class=\"card-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-title\">Why Wikipedia's cofounder wants to replace the online encyclopedia with the blockchain</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-body\">   <p>Jimmy Wales, who co-founded Wikipedia 25 years ago, says the online encyclopaedia needs a radical overhaul and that blockchain technology could provide the change that is needed. At a technology conference recently, Wales stated that he believed Wikipedia\u2019s volunteer-driven model has struggled with issues including declining editor participation, governance disputes and growing mistrust over content moderation.</p>\n           <p>Under his proposal he stated that articles and edits would be recorded on a public blockchain effectively creating a transparent, tamper-resistant history of everyone who has contributed. He stated that members of the public could become contributors to the programme, earning digital tokens for verified edits, in the hope of attracting experts in the specific field. Mr Wales believed that 'smart' contracts might be helpful in creating a more well rounded editorial platform.</p>\n           <p>Wales hoped that his plans would make it harder for the site to be manipulated and that giving power to a broader group of people would reduce complaints about the current smaller administrator groups. Those critical of his ideas appear unconvinced that his blockchain systems can be scaled up to handle Wikipedia's popularity and warn that token incentives might encourage low-quality edits.</p>\n           <p>The Wikimedia Foundation stated that it was always interested in new ideas but that remaining non profit, whist embracing its community is key. The future of Wikipedia appears to be uncertain. We can only wait and see whether it can reinvent itself whilst remaining a trusted brand.</p></div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "DataExportTag": "instruct_c3",
                "QuestionID": "QID1219691460",
                "QuestionType": "DB",
                "Selector": "TB",
                "DataVisibility": {
