                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay.\nYour teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his\ndraft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring\nyou that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like\nwriting style. <br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns\nabout students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your\nprofessor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be\nidentified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three\nsample essays using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_1_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_1_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>The Nobel Peace Prize was awarded today to the International Campaign for Nuclear Abolition to honour the decades-long effort to eliminate atomic weapons and reduce the risk of a future catastrophic war. The coalition that has been praised by the Norwegian Nobel Committee for building global momentum behind the Treaty on the Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons, is made up of grassroots activists, scientists, and survivors of nuclear testing were. In their speech, the committee said the group had \"reframed the debate on nuclear deterrence by highlighting the consequences of any use of Nuclear weapons.</p>\n           <p>Accepting the award in Oslo, executive director Maria Santos called the prize \"a tribute to ordinary people who refuse to live under the shadow of annihilation.\" She urged nuclear-armed states to join together to talk about disarming and invest instead in health, climate and education. Leaders from several countries welcomed the decision, while officials in nuclear powers cautioned that deterrence remains essential to national security.</p>\n           <p>Analysts said the prize could intensify diplomatic pressure ahead of next year's non-proliferation review conference, where divisions between nuclear and non-nuclear states are expected. Founded in 2007, the campaign now includes more than 600 partner organizations worldwide and has focused on survivor testimony and youth activism. with the aim to get many more to join, so we can rid the world of this threat. Committee chair Anne Lunde said the honor recognizes \"persistent moral leadership.\"</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_2_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_2_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>The Egyptian Red Sea islands of Tiran and Sanafir have been officially returned to Saudia Arabia. This transfer of sovereignty of the islands has been met with opposition to the transfer.</p>\n           <p>The government believes that the transfer will foster increased economic ties and greater collaboration between the two countries, and will also restore rightful ownership to Saudi Arabia.</p>\n           <p>Opponents of the move have been quick to respond and have challenged the transfer in court. This has created greater tensions nationally and sparked national debates centered around the how the transfer has occurred. Officials have stated that movement across the region will be unaffected and governed by international agreements.</p>\n           <p>Saudi Arabia welcomed the news suggesting that it clears the way for increased cooperation between the two governments. Official handover of the islands is expected pending final ratification of the agreement.</p>\n           <p>Reporters and news outlets suggest that domestic unrest could take place resulting in further tensions between the two countries.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_3_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_3_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t__PRIME_3_PARAGRAPHS_HTML__\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n\t\n<br />\nWith these samples in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon's essay</strong>:\n<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__STIMULUS_TOPIC__</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n           <p>Jimmy Wales, who co-founded Wikipedia 25 years ago, says the online encyclopaedia needs a radical overhaul and that blockchain technology could provide the change that is needed. At a technology conference recently, Wales stated that he believed Wikipedia\u2019s volunteer-driven model has struggled with issues including declining editor participation, governance disputes and growing mistrust over content moderation.</p>\n           <p>Under his proposal he stated that articles and edits would be recorded on a public blockchain effectively creating a transparent, tamper-resistant history of everyone who has contributed. He stated that members of the public could become contributors to the programme, earning digital tokens for verified edits, in the hope of attracting experts in the specific field. Mr Wales believed that 'smart' contracts might be helpful in creating a more well rounded editorial platform.</p>\n           <p>Wales hoped that his plans would make it harder for the site to be manipulated and that giving power to a broader group of people would reduce complaints about the current smaller administrator groups. Those critical of his ideas appear unconvinced that his blockchain systems can be scaled up to handle Wikipedia's popularity and warn that token incentives might encourage low-quality edits.</p>\n           <p>The Wikimedia Foundation stated that it was always interested in new ideas but that remaining non profit, whist embracing its community is key. The future of Wikipedia appears to be uncertain. We can only wait and see whether it can reinvent itself whilst remaining a trusted brand.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n",
                "QuestionJS": false
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691461",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "Brandon's text is shown again sentence by sentence, each followed by an editable text box prefill...",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "Brandon's text is shown again sentence by sentence, each followed by an\neditable text box prefilled with that sentence.\nMake any changes you think will help the text read convincingly as\nhuman-written and unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated. You may rephrase,\nadd, or remove content as you see fit. If you choose to merge sentences, enter\nthe combined version in the first relevant text box and leave the following\none(s) empty. You can also split sentences by writing multiple sentences within\na single text box. Edit as many text boxes as you feel are needed.\n<br /><br />",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "DataExportTag": "edit_c3",
                "QuestionID": "QID1219691461",
                "QuestionType": "TE",
                "Selector": "ML",
                "DataVisibility": {
