                },
                "GradingData": [],
                "Language": [],
                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay.\nYour teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his\ndraft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring\nyou that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like\nwriting style. <br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns\nabout students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your\nprofessor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be\nidentified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three\nsample essays using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_1_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_1_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>Barbara Bush, the former first lady of the United States and matriarch of one of the country\u2019s most prominent political families, has died at the age of 92. A family member has confirmed that Barbara passed away piecefully at her home in Houston, surrounded by loved ones.</p>\n           <p>Barbara was the wife of the 41st president, George H.W. and served as the first lady from 1989 to 1993.  Barbara was known for her trademark white hair, sharp wit and outspoken advocacy for literacy. She founded the Barbara Bush Foundation for Family Litercay in 1989, helping raise millions of dollars to promote programs nationwide.</p>\n           <p>She was born in New York City in 1925 by the name Barbara Pierce, she married  in 1945 and raised six children, including former President George W. Bush and former Florida Governor Jeb Bush. She was widely regarded as a reassuring presence within the Bush family and a genuine voice in American politics.</p>\n           <p>Tributes poured in praising her dedication to public service, family and country. Funeral arrangements are expected to be announced in the coming days. She will be remembered for her resilience and quiet dignity throughout her life.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_2_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_2_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>Scientists have discovered a prehistoric worm-like creature they describe as \u201cstrange beyond measure,\u201d showing an unusual branch of early animal evolution. The fossilized remains were found in 520\u2011million\u2011year\u2011old marine sediments in western China. They revealed a soft-bodied organism with a tubular form, ringed segments, and a circular mouth lined with sharp, backward-facing spines.</p>\n           <p>Measuring just a few inches long, the creature likely lived on the seafloor during the Cambrian Period. Researchers believe, it used its spiny mouth to latch onto prey or organic material, drawing food into a simple digestive tract. Despite its modest size, the worm\u2019s anatomy is quite unique.</p>\n           <p>\u201cIt\u2019s strange beyond measure,\u201d said lead paleontologist Dr. Li Wen. \u201cIts combination of features doesn\u2019t neatly fit into any known group, living or extinct.\u201d Advanced imaging techniques revealed preserved muscle fibers and traces of internal organs, offering rare insight into soft-bodied animals that seldom fossilize.</p>\n           <p>The discovery suggests, that early marine ecosystems, were more diverse  than previously understood. Scientists hope further study will clarify where this creature fits in evolution, and what it reveals.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_3_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_3_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t__PRIME_3_PARAGRAPHS_HTML__\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n\t\n<br />\nWith these samples in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon's essay</strong>:\n<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__STIMULUS_TOPIC__</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n           <p>A renowned quantum physicist,  Dr. Amelia Hart, has been named Australian of the Year for her pioneering research in quantum computing as well as her advocacy for science education. The award was announced at a ceremony in Canberra on Tuesday night. It  recognized Hart\u2019s leadership in developing ultra-stable qubits that could accelerate the arrival of practical quantum technologies.</p>\n           <p>Hart is a professor at the University of Sydney and director of the National Quantum Innovation Centre. She has spent the last 20 years advancing methods to reduce error rates in quantum processors. Her team\u2019s breakthrough last year demonstrated a scalable architecture capable of operating at room temperature. Experts say this is a milestone could lower costs and expand commercial applications.</p>\n           <p>Hart has championed greater access to STEM education for girls and students in regional communities beyond the laboratory. She has launched mentorship programs, advised government on critical technology policy, and spoken widely about the ethical implications of quantum breakthroughs.</p>\n           <p>Prime Minister said Hart embodies \u201ccuriosity, collaboration and courage.\u201d Hart accepted the award and dedicated the honor to her students and colleagues. She urged sustained investment in research to secure Australia\u2019s place in the global quantum race. She called the moment a reminder of science\u2019s power to unite nations through shared discovery.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n",
                "QuestionJS": false
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691491",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "Brandon's text is shown again sentence by sentence, each followed by an editable text box prefill...",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "Brandon's text is shown again sentence by sentence, each followed by an\neditable text box prefilled with that sentence.\nMake any changes you think will help the text read convincingly as\nhuman-written and unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated. You may rephrase,\nadd, or remove content as you see fit. If you choose to merge sentences, enter\nthe combined version in the first relevant text box and leave the following\none(s) empty. You can also split sentences by writing multiple sentences within\na single text box. Edit as many text boxes as you feel are needed.\n<br /><br />",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "DataExportTag": "edit_c13",
